[Patient] Can you recommend exercise for me with my heart failure? 
[Healthcare Educator] Walking or light jogging in your safe neighborhood can help improve your heart health. 
[Patient] What if I can't afford a gym membership or equipment? 
[Healthcare Educator] You can do bodyweight exercises at home, like squats or push-ups, to stay active. 
[Patient] Will walking alone be enough to help my heart failure? 
[Healthcare Educator] Regular walking can be beneficial, but adding in some light resistance exercises can further improve your heart health. 
[Patient] Are there any community resources for me to access for exercise? 
[Healthcare Educator] Look for local walking groups or free fitness classes in your neighborhood to stay active.